annotationA: Rpb5, isoform A; DNA binding; DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; mitotic G2 DNA damage checkpoint
annotationB: Probable prefoldin subunit 2; Binds specifically to cytosolic chaperonin (c-CPN) and transfers target proteins to it. Binds to nascent polypeptide chain and promotes folding in an environment in which there are many competing pathways for nonnative proteins (By similarity)
